OMFG I feel you on this. I came out as Trans (MTF) about a year ago and Bi. Thankfully I don’t have many friends and don’t talk into my family so I know my support network is supportive because I’m selective to begin with. But you need to cut these people out of your lives right now. Just block them everywhere and if your supportive friends are friend with them just explain the situation. You shouldn’t tolerate it what so ever. Just block them and never talk to them again. There’s no need to get bullied because you feel like you’re the opposite gender of your birth gender. It’s perfectly fine. Also who gives a F if you’re gay. If you’re hitting on them then yes they can worry about it but it’s none of their business. You’re still their friend.

You go !! I wish I did that when I cut contact but I didn’t. Just blocked her number, my father, the home number and my brother. I felt as a scapegoat for my mothers issues as well and it formed into a sever depression myself  and massive debt to go with it. You’re mental and physical health is more important then them and while it’s sad it is something that you HAD to do and I commend you for that step.
